      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Arts, Briefly report April 26 about Billboard chart; Avril Lavine's new album sold 286,000 copies in first week</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A report in the ''Arts, Briefly'' column yesterday, about the weekly Billboard album chart, misstated the number of copies that Avril Lavigne's new album, ''The Best Damn Thing,'' sold in its first week of release to open at No. 1 on the chart. It was 286,000, not 381,000.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A report in the ''Arts, Briefly'' column yesterday, about the weekly Billboard album chart, misstated the number of copies that Avril Lavigne's new album, ''The Best Damn Thing,'' sold in its first week of release to open at No. 1 on the chart. It was 286,000, not 381,000.</p>
      </block>
